					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A lot of TVs assume that anything coming in on HDMI is formatted to assume overscan. Because the first HDTVs were 1080i CRTs, consumer electronics HDTV signals are formatted for nominal CRT overscan. LCD HDTVs have to enlarge the image by a few percent in order to compensate for this. Check your TV's menu for a &quot;1:1&quot; or &quot;game&quot; mode.</div>

